  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="ITA72">
<l>pōtaṟintu vāṉaraṅkaḷ pūñcuṉaipuk kāṅkalarnta</l>
<l>pōtarintu koṇṭēttum pōtuḷḷam – pōtu</l>
<l>maṇivēṅ kaṭavaṉ malaraṭikkē cella</l>
<l>vaṇivēṅ kaṭavaṉpē rāyntu</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>When, knowing the time, the monkeys enter flower pools, cut off the buds</l>
<l>blooming there [and] praise with them, [then it is] time, heart,</l>
<l>to go to the blossom feet of him from the sapphire[-blue] Vēṅkaṭam,</l>
<l>selecting the names of him from ornate Vēṅkaṭam.<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">Tārkkatīrttar Rāmānujācāryar connects pōtu (l. 2) and aṇi (l. 4), in order to read a second imperative: “adorn with buds”.</note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
